    "client_msg_id": "bbeed0d8-3c09-4fd7-9293-2d16b9d692b0",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "That's fair and good way to describe it.  Already on the web, we look up code (big and small), find libraries or snippets, package them up, and pull them in.  Over time this process has improved.  We have Stackoverflow instead of random forums.  We have GitHub instead of SourceForge.  CPAN-like systems are the rule rather than the exception.  What sharp edges remain?  What frictions prevent a smoother experience?",
    "user": "UA14TGLTC",
