  {
    "client_msg_id": "b901ee55-50df-4c76-af96-ecb184c1c875",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "The frictions include not being able to immediately execute, experiment with, and discuss any code snippet you see _by default_ (i.e. as opposed to only on special websites which embed CodePen). In this hypothetical environment, whatever changes you make can be published/bookmarked somewhere with a single click. Those changes can be made publicly visible and available for discussion. Thus we don’t have to write and run code by signing up to Github, forking and cloning to your local file system, setting up a dev environment, pushing changes upstream etc… It’s just about the UX details in my opinion.",
    "user": "UCGAK10LS",
