    "client_msg_id": "bfe73ef7-2ed5-46db-9102-6fc6bc076f27",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "<@UCGAK10LS> I am enthusiastic about the general idea and have though about it a bit and hope to explore the design space a little in this conversation.\n\nWe have in mind a certain experience, yet being \"just about the UX details\" seems to underestimate the difference from what we generally do now.  You say \"thus we don’t have to [set up a local] dev environment.\"  Do you have an entirely online experience (no local) in mind or a more of a seamless synchronization to a dedicated local client/browser?  Either seems to amount to a whole kit and caboodle, not just a better interface to an existing backend.",
